76561198079202405,Recommended,252250,31301020,Posted: 22 April,all,The Last Nigel,"It seems this game doesn't do a good job of showing what it is/is not.Maia *is not* a game where you can micro-manage people, fiddle with spreadsheets and build queues.Maia *is* a game where you try to build a base with (and for) a bunch of colonists that will allow them to survive on a hostile alien world. The colonists handle (most) prioritisation of tasks, they handle what they will and will not build, they handle most of their needs; the game is working out what rooms or equipment they need to fulfill those needs and explore the world they have landed on, without dying.The lack of build queues is not a bug, the lack of spreadsheets containing task prioritisations and other ways to fiddle is not a bug. The developer has (rightly) decided these things exist in other games to patch over bad AI and we have just normalised them. In software development these things are called 'leaky abstractions' and are not desirable.It's been a long, hard slog to get the AI to the point where it works properly (AI is hard, BTW) and doesn't eventually do something dumb and kill itself, but with 0.61 I think we're at the point where it works pretty well.The one big minus with this game seems to be usability: the game doesn't show the player what it is (note: I don't use the word 'explain' here), meaning users have the expectation of spreadsheets and tweaking, and the build menus are cumbersome and slow to use.Maia is also working great for me on Linux (AMD/Mesa drivers). Simon Roth also is an alright bloke who's genuinely dedicated to finishing his game.==============Original, stupid review, which I still stand behind:Simon Roth is a great man, he has great hair. The best hair, everybody knows that. He has the best hair in gaming and he likes me a lot. Everyone likes me especially Simon Roth and his hair.I predicted Maia is going to be a great game, and it is, it is. 0.61 is the best game from early access in 2013 that might be released in 2017. That's what I said back in 2012 and I was right. And you know what goes into games like this? A lot of good stuff. Like Frustum Culling. Good stuff. Great hair. And I predicted that, and I was right."
