,Recommended,252250,27284484,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,Luke Nukem [Linux Only],"I didn't manage to get much time on this game due to study taking priority, but from the miniscle amount of time I did get I can say this; it's fun!The game is a simulation of sorts of trying to colonise an inhospitable planet. There are many dangers present, such as colonist incompetence, your own incompetence (yep! My first play and everyone died of hypothermia), planetary dangers (earthquakes), equipment failures, solar flares/radiation. A bit like a Sim-something game, scaled down and focused on the premise of colonising - well okay, similar in scope to ""The Sims"", but Mars!Colonists all have their own personalities and skillsets, and as such are more/less suited for particular tasks. Getting a random song or poem from one is a charming touch.It is a very interesting game, and one that is gaining more depth and complexity as time goes on. It may be early-access alpha level, but the game already has more than enough in it to entertain for hours; I can see myself getting lost in it easily.The developer is incredibly active, both on social media, as well as posting a game changelog on their website and in the games news section on Steam. Seriously, check out the news section! They are very passionate about their game, and this shows heavily in playing it.If you like the idea or premise behind ""The Sims"" but didn't like the mundane setting of it, maybe this will tickle your fancy?Oh and did I mention it has humour?"
