,Recommended,252250,7915886,"Posted: 4 December, 2013",all,[|||] Magnum Force,"Maia is basically one of many atempts to juice up an old concept. Throughout teh years many games about colony survival hit the games market and only a couple gained a place in our memories. e.g. Outpost, Space Colony, Startopia. But, most of those games are lost in the vast endless space of cybernet.So, how able is Maia in obtaining a place amongst our memory?At this point, it's a buy and forget game. Not because of the way it looks, it's probably one the best looking colony survival games out there, but because of the way it tries to create an atmosphere.I don't know exactly why, but something is missing.. The feeling of survival. Why should I build s**t if I don't care. Why should I research things if I don't see the point in doing so.This is probably because of the lack of any solid plot and future goal that keeps me interested.Yea, sure, my goal is to survive. Yea, whatever, I'm playing a game, I want some glittering prices along the way and some motivation to do some crazy things. I'm playing a game to escape the dull side of reality, so please, don't show me my daily struggle.In other words, we need a good Visual Novel style content / plot / story. We need interesting characters and social dillema's.If Maia is able to provide us with those things in the near future, well, in that case we might have ourselves a winner.But, as long as it stays the way it is (Bugs not taken into account) it's a dull experience.My final verdict, which might sound strange, is ""Yes""not bad, actually pretty good, because it shows good potential.On the other hand, I won't hesitate to put out a huge ""NO"" if the developers don't change the ""Living"" part of the game. The social interaction, story and story driven motivation."
