,Recommended,252250,8110756,"Posted: 18 December, 2013",all,Nameless Oblivion,"Amended Review - As of Maia 0.58. (Original Review 12/2013)Still an early Access game at this point.MAIA is rough. Still ""Alpha"" rough.There's great potential here, but I'm rather hesitant to recommend a game this unpolished and unfinished to anyone. For now, I'd advise waiting, and returning when the team delivers that final software.However...If you're willing to tolerate the slow pace of development necessitated by the small team, then I do really think that there's a gem on the way here. It's still early days, but the game has come a long way since I first played it in 2013, and the development team has continued to roll out updates, including feature additions and bugfixes indicative of ongoing long-term development and support.As long as you understand that you're getting in on an alpha, this might be worth a look. Just recognize that it's not a finished product yet, and given the pace of development will not be ready for that final rollout for some time."
